Olympic Ice</link></activity>
</entertainment>
</psychological_feature>
</act>
</show>
</sport>
</event>
</diversion>
</it>, on <channel wordnetid="106259898" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../826/77826.xml">
USA Network</link></channel>
 with co-hosts <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<skater wordnetid="110604491" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../072/945072.xml">
Scott Hamilton</link></skater>
</person>
, <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<skater wordnetid="110604491" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../326/728326.xml">
Dick Button</link></skater>
</person>
, and <link>
Jamie Salé</link> &amp; <skater wordnetid="110604491" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../329/372329.xml">
David Pelletier</link></skater>
. Carillo also served as a host and correspondent for <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../761/1681761.xml">
NBC Sports</link>' coverage of the <fundamental_quantity wordnetid="113575869" confidence="0.8">
<time_period wordnetid="115113229" confidence="0.8">
<festival wordnetid="115162388" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../745/77745.xml">
2008 Summer Olympics</link></festival>
</time_period>
</fundamental_quantity>
. <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>
<p>

Carillo was a <fundamental_quantity wordnetid="113575869" confidence="0.8">
<time_period wordnetid="115113229" confidence="0.8">
<festival wordnetid="115162388" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../745/77745.xml">
