</time_period>
</fundamental_quantity>
 correspondent for <network wordnetid="108434259" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../780/21780.xml">
NBC</link></network>
, hosting the "Olympic Late Night" program and focusing on cultural commentary/"slice of life" pieces about China.</p>

</ss1>
<ss1>
<st>
Tennis coverage</st>
<p>

Prior to joining CBS Sports, Carillo provided tennis analysis for the <channel wordnetid="106259898" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../826/77826.xml">
USA Network</link></channel>
 for six years beginning in 1980. She currently fills that role for <channel wordnetid="106259898" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../795/77795.xml">
ESPN</link></channel>
. Aside from her commentary duties, Carillo serves as a correspondent for the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../530/4765530.xml">
HBO Sports</link> magazine program <it><beginning wordnetid="100235435" confidence="0.8">
<change wordnetid="100191142" confidence="0.8">
<sport wordnetid="100523513" confidence="0.8">
<show wordnetid="100520257" confidence="0.8">
